ke of business scandals and the financial crisis. The effort restrained imperial CEOs but could not bridge the divide between workers and owners. Wages lagged behind investor returns, feeding the inequality identified by Occupy Wall Street. And labor’s slide continued.A compelling blend of history, economics, and politics, Labor in the Age of Finance explores the paradox of capital bestowing power to labor in the tumultuous era of Enron, Lehman Brothers, and Dodd-Frank.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aCorporate governancezUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aCorporate governancezUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aFinancializationzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aFinancializationzUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aLabor movementzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aLabor movementzUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aLabor unionszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aLabor unionszUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Labor.2bisacsh  aAFL-CIO.  aAmerican labor unions.  aCalPERS.  aCampaign GM.  aCarl Kaysen.  aEmployee Retirement Security Act.  aFASB.  aGoldman Sachs.  aIBEW.  aJimmy Carter.  aJimmy Hoffa.  aLloyd Ulman.  aMichael Eisner.  aMichael Ovitz.  aNLRB.  aNational Labor Relations Board.  aPiketty.  aRalph Nader.  aRonald Reagan.  aSEC.  aSaul Alinsky.  aTaft-Hartley Act.  aTeamsters.  aTreaty of Detroit.  aUAW.  aUFCW.  aUnited Auto Workers.  aUnited Steelworkers.  aWalter Reuther.  acollective bargaining.  ahistory of labor.  alabor reform.  aorganized labor.  ashareholder activism.  ashareholder democracy.  aunion investors.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2021 Englishz978311075404908iTitle is part of eBook 